 673:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** 
 674:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** /**
 675:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @defgroup ComplexFFT Complex FFT Functions
 676:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** 
 677:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 678:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The Fast Fourier Transform (FFT) is an efficient algorithm for computing the
 679:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    Discrete Fourier Transform (DFT).  The FFT can be orders of magnitude faster
 680:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    than the DFT, especially for long lengths.
 681:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The algorithms described in this section
 682:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    operate on complex data.  A separate set of functions is devoted to handling
 683:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    of real sequences.
 684:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 685:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    There are separate algorithms for handling floating-point, Q15, and Q31 data
 686:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    types.  The algorithms available for each data type are described next.
 687:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 688:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The FFT functions operate in-place.  That is, the array holding the input data
 689:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    will also be used to hold the corresponding result.  The input data is complex
 690:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    and contains <code>2*fftLen</code> interleaved values as shown below.
 691:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    <pre>{real[0], imag[0], real[1], imag[1], ...} </pre>
 692:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The FFT result will be contained in the same array and the frequency domain
 693:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    values will have the same interleaving.
 694:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** 
 695:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par Floating-point
 696:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The floating-point complex FFT uses a mixed-radix algorithm.  Multiple radix-8
 697:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    stages are performed along with a single radix-2 or radix-4 stage, as needed.
 698:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The algorithm supports lengths of [16, 32, 64, ..., 4096] and each length uses
 699:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    a different twiddle factor table.
 700:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 701:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The function uses the standard FFT definition and output values may grow by a
 702:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    factor of <code>fftLen</code> when computing the forward transform.  The
 703:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    inverse transform includes a scale of <code>1/fftLen</code> as part of the
 704:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    calculation and this matches the textbook definition of the inverse FFT.
 705:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 706:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    For the MVE version, the new arm_cfft_init_f32 initialization function is
 707:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    <b>mandatory</b>. <b>Compilation flags are available to include only the require
 708:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    needed FFTs.</b> Other FFT versions can continue to be initialized as
 709:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    explained below.
 710:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 711:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    For versions not targeting Helium or Neon, pre-initialized data structures conta
 712:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    and bit reversal tables are provided and defined in <code>arm_const_structs.h</c
 713:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    this header in your function and then pass one of the constant structures as
 714:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    an argument to arm_cfft_f32.  For example:
 715:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccSWltYc.s 			page 14


 716:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    <code>arm_cfft_f32(arm_cfft_sR_f32_len64, pSrc, 1, 1)</code>
 717:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 718:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    computes a 64-point inverse complex FFT including bit reversal.
 719:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    The data structures are treated as constant data and not modified during the
 720:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    calculation.  The same data structure can be reused for multiple transforms
 721:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    including mixing forward and inverse transforms.
 722:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 723:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    Earlier releases of the library provided separate radix-2 and radix-4
 724:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    algorithms that operated on floating-point data.  These functions are still
 725:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    provided but are deprecated.  The older functions are slower and less general
 726:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    than the new functions.
 727:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @par
 728:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    An example of initialization of the constants for the arm_cfft_f32 function foll
 729:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****   @code
 730:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    const static arm_cfft_instance_f32 *S;
 731:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    ...
 732:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                    switch (length) {
 733:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                      case 16:
 734:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                        S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len16;
 735:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                        break;
 736:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                      case 32:
 737:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                        S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len32;
 738:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                        break;
 739:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c ****                      case 64:
